SECTION 1: PROJECT OVERVIEW (UPDATED)

Project Purpose

- Full-stack Student Task Manager: let students create, track, prioritize, and complete tasks (assignments, projects, study items) with analytics and a responsive UI.

Main Problem Solved

- Centralize student tasks with due dates, priority and subject tagging, easy filtering, and a small analytics dashboard to surface urgency and completion metrics.

Target Users

- Students and educators needing a light task-tracking dashboard.

High-Level Workflow (current)

- User registers and logs in via frontend forms. Login returns a short-lived JWT access token and the server issues a persistent refresh token stored server-side and sent as an HttpOnly cookie.
- Frontend persists auth (access token + user) in `localStorage` and attaches `Authorization: Bearer <token>` to API requests. On 401 the client attempts `POST /api/users/refresh` (using cookie) to obtain a new access token and retries the original request once.
- Users create tasks with title, description, optional subject, due date and priority; tasks default to `PENDING` and `MEDIUM` priority when omitted.
- Users view tasks, filter by status and priority, search by text, edit tasks, mark tasks `COMPLETED` (no revert to `PENDING`), and delete tasks.
- Dashboard fetches analytics (completion %, overdue, dueThisWeek, priority/subject distributions) which frontend renders with Chart.js via react-chartjs-2.

Major Modules Implemented (current)

- Frontend (React + Vite, pnpm): `src/context/AuthContext.jsx` (auth + localStorage), API clients (`src/api/auth.js`, `src/api/tasks.js`, `src/api/analytics.js`) with refresh-on-401 logic, components: `AppLayout`, `Sidebar`, `TaskForm`, `TaskCard`, `TaskFilters`, `TaskStats`, charts and pages: `Landing`, `Login`, `Register`, `Dashboard`, `MyTasks`.
- Backend (Spring Boot, Java 21, Maven): controllers, services, repositories, DTOs, JPA entities, security utilities for JWT, refresh token entity/service, `JwtAuthenticationFilter`, `SecurityConfig` with global CORS configuration, and `RefreshToken` persistence.

