SECTION 9: APPLICATION WORKFLOW

Step-by-step user journey (exact code-based flow):

1. Registration

- User visits `/register` (frontend `Register.jsx`), fills `name,email,password` and submits.
- Frontend posts to `POST /api/users/register`.
- Backend validates DTO; if valid and email not existing, `UserService` encodes password with BCrypt and saves `User`. Backend responds with `UserResponseDTO` and success message.
- Frontend navigates the user to `/login` on success.

2. Login

- User visits `/login`, submits `email,password`.
- Frontend posts to `POST /api/users/login`.
- Backend validates DTO, looks up user, checks password via `PasswordEncoder.matches`. On success it returns `UserResponseDTO`.
- Frontend `Login.jsx` receives response, calls `login(result.data)` from `AuthContext`, which stores the user object in `localStorage` and sets in-memory `user`. Frontend navigates to `/dashboard`.

3. Dashboard Access

- Route `/dashboard` is protected by `AppLayout` which checks `useAuth().user`; if missing, it redirects to `/login`.
- Dashboard component uses `getTasks(user.id)` and `getTaskSummary(user.id)` to populate UI. It computes overdue/due-this-week counts client-side.

4. Task Creation

- From `/tasks` (`MyTasks.jsx`), user fills `TaskForm` and submits.
- Frontend calls `createTask(user.id, form)` which sends `POST /api/tasks/create/{userId}` with `TaskRequestDTO` JSON.
- Backend `TaskService.createTask` validates and saves a `Task` (defaults: status PENDING, priority MEDIUM if missing) and returns `TaskResponseDTO`.
- Frontend resets form and reloads tasks.

5. Task Update

- User clicks Edit on a task (`TaskCard`), frontend populates `TaskForm` with task data and sets `editingTask`.
- On submit, `MyTasks` calls `updateTask(taskId, user.id, form)` sending `PUT /api/tasks/update/{taskId}?userId={user.id}`.
- Backend checks ownership `findByIdAndUserId`, applies update rules (prevents COMPLETED->PENDING), saves, and returns updated `TaskResponseDTO`.
- Frontend refreshes list and clears editing state.

6. Task Completion

- User clicks Complete on a PENDING task; frontend confirms via `window.confirm` and then calls `updateTask` with `status: 'COMPLETED'`.
- Backend performs update and returns updated data. Frontend reloads tasks and shows success.

7. Search & Filtering

- Frontend fetches tasks (optionally with `status` query param when a status filter is applied) and applies client-side search (filtering by title/description/subject) and priority filter.
- No server-side full-text search; filtering by priority is done client-side.

8. Logout

- User clicks Logout in `Sidebar`, which calls `logout()` from `AuthContext` that clears `user` state and `localStorage.removeItem('user')`.
- Protected routes redirect to `/login` after logout.

